@page "/documentation/api/codegeneration"

<div class="container mx-auto p-6 font-mono">
    <section class="mb-8">

        <!-- Title and Introduction -->
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Code Generation Guide</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">AiDesigner provides seamless code generation capabilities for your programs. Once your program is ready, you can obtain the generated code in multiple languages to easily integrate it into your projects.</p>

        <!-- Finding Generated Code -->
        <div class="mb-4 bg-gray-700 p-4 rounded">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Finding Your Generated Code</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">To locate the generated code for your program, simply:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-4 ml-6 mb-2">
                <li>Access the program you've created within AiDesigner.</li>
                <li>Click on the 'Code Generation' option or similar.</li>
                <li>Choose the respective tab or dropdown for the desired programming language.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Supported Languages -->
        <div class="mb-4 bg-gray-700 p-4 rounded">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Supported Languages</h3>
            <p class="mb-4">AiDesigner currently supports code generation for the following languages:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-4 ml-6 mb-2">
                <li>C# (C Sharp)</li>
                <li>Python</li>
                <li>JavaScript (JS)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Note on Integration -->
        <div class="mb-4 bg-gray-700 p-4 rounded">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Integration</h3>
            <p>After obtaining the generated code, you can seamlessly integrate it into your application or platform. Ensure you adhere to any dependencies or prerequisites mentioned within the code comments or documentation for a smooth integration.</p>
        </div>

    </section>
</div>

